This is my second time returning to this location . First visit wasn’t that great but decided to give it a second chance . Nope never again . I ordered Mac and cheese and bbq fried chicken . Mac and cheese is suppose to be the same portion as rice in this case since I’m not getting no rice . The Mac and cheese was on the end I watched the lady scoop the left over( one scoop) and give me . I asked if this is the portion because clearly it wasn’t meal portioned for a $13 dollar meal she had the nerve to say yes. It should have been two scoops but because she was trying to stretch the Mac and cheese and fill 3 other meals she gave me scraps .  They are robbing people blind. I will not return . I will stick to bed stuy fish fry or fisherman cove where the portions are good. A large meal is meant to share amongst two ppl which clearly can’t be done with their meals. Even when purchasing a small from other places I am able to have food left over . This was not the case at Peppas. It certainly varies on who serves you because last time I got a good portion but the food was way to spicy. They had a young boy must be a relative serving that clearly had no clue what he was doing . I was way to tired to argue over food so I just took it left . Disgusted and turned off to even eat it at this point. I’m super annoyed because the portion is still not worth the money but I know I will not be returning!!!
